QGridLayout: A layout manager that arranges widgets in a grid of rows and columns.

Tlacitko: Imports your custom button/widget class from the Tlacitko.py file to be used as player blocks.

hra_widget & QVBoxLayout: Creates a new screen container and a vertical master layout to hold the grid and the "Back" button.

QGridLayout: Initializes a grid to organize player counters side-by-side.

seznam_barev: A predefined list of hex codes used to give each player a unique background color.

for i in range(pocet_h):

Creates a new instance of Tlacitko for each player.

radek = i // 2 & sloupec = i % 2: Mathematical floor division and modulo used to arrange widgets into a 2-column layout automatically.

btn_zpet.clicked: Connects the "Back" button to a function that returns the user to the main menu.

setCurrentWidget: Switches the QStackedWidget view from the menu to the newly created game screen.
